  "ai_overview": {
    "text_blocks": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "snippet": "To apply for a passport, fill out the application form, get a passport photo, and gather original proof of citizenship and identity with copies. Submit these documents in person at a designated post office, local government office, or consulate, and pay the applicable passport fees.",
        "snippet_links": [
          {
            "link": "https://travel.state.gov/en/passports.html"
          }
        ],
        "snippet_highlighted_words": [
          "fill out the application form, get a passport photo, and gather original proof of citizenship and identity with copies. Submit these documents in person at a designated post office, local government office, or consulate, and pay the applicable passport fees"
        ],
        "reference_indexes": [
          0,
          1,
          2
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "snippet": "If you are applying for a U.S. Passport, follow these specific steps:"
      },
      {
        "type": "list",
        "list": [
          {
            "snippet": "Complete the Application: Fill out Form DS-11 online or print it out to fill by hand. Do not sign it until you are instructed to do so in front of an acceptance agent.",
            "snippet_links": [
              {
                "link": "https://www.usa.gov/apply-adult-passport"
              }
            ],
            "reference_indexes": [
              3,
              4
            ]
          },
          {
            "snippet": "Gather Documents: You need original proof of U.S. citizenship (e.g., birth certificate or naturalization certificate) and a valid photo ID (e.g., driver's license), plus clear photocopies of the front and back of each.",
            "snippet_links": [
              {
                "link": "https://www.usa.gov/apply-adult-passport"
              }
            ],
            "reference_indexes": [
              3
            ]
          },
          {
            "snippet": "Get a Photo: Obtain a recent, 2\u00d72 inch color passport photo with a white background and a neutral expression.",
            "snippet_links": [
              {
                "link": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=S9HInFUlXxU&t=113"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "snippet": "Pay Fees: Check or money order is typically required for the application fee, while a separate fee is required for the execution/acceptance facility. Use the Travel.gov Fee Calculator to check exact totals.",
            "snippet_links": [
              {
                "link": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FD0wwBbBb1A"
              }
            ],
            "reference_indexes": [
              5
            ]
          },
          {
            "snippet": "Submit in Person: Schedule an appointment at a local acceptance facility, such as a post office or library. You can find locations and book online using the USPS Passport Appointment Scheduler\n\n.",
            "snippet_links": [
              {
                "text": "USPS Passport Appointment Scheduler",
                "link": "https://www.usps.com/international/passports.htm"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "reference_indexes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "snippet": "Note for applicants currently in Santa Cruz: You will need to apply at the U.S. Consular Agency in Santa Cruz (Calle G Esquina Avenida Salvador, Piso 4). Appointments must be scheduled in advance through the U.S. Embassy in Bolivia Website\n\n.",
        "snippet_links": [
          {
            "text": "U.S. Embassy in Bolivia Website",
            "link": "https://bo.usembassy.gov/passports/important-passport-information/"
          }
        ],
        "reference_indexes": [
          2
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "snippet": "If you can tell me which country's passport you are applying for, I can give you the exact official forms and direct you to the right local government portals."
      }
    ],
